The paper deals with adversarial attacks and defenses in machine learning, specifically for ReLU networks. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, but the most likely ones are cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision), as these are the areas where adversarial attacks have been extensively studied. The paper also discusses regularization schemes, which are relevant to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper proposes a new method for enforcing robustness, which is relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
